%N A357733 Integer lengths of the sides of such regular hexagons that a polyline described in A356047 exists.
%C A357733 The length of the side of the hexagon is determined using a triangular grid depending on the number of links, which reduces to nontrivial solutions of the Pell equation x^2 - 3y^2 = 1 for even x.
%H A357733 Alexander M. Domashenko, <a href="https://elementy.ru/problems/2606/Zmeyka_v_shestiugolnike">Problem: Snake in a hexagon</a> (in Russian).
